'''治療性超聲波'''通常指的是用於[[治療|治療]]用途的[[超聲波|超聲波]]。包括[[高强度聚焦超声|高强度聚焦超声]]、[[碎石術|碎石術]]、超聲波給藥、超聲波[[止血|止血]]、[[癌癥治療|癌癥治療]]以及協助[[血栓溶解|血栓溶解]]。<ref name="#1">{{cite journal|doi=10.1517/17425247.2012.739603| title=Ultrasound-Enhanced Drug Delivery for Cancer|author=Steven Mo, Constantin-C Coussios, Len Seymour & Robert Carlisle |journal=Expert Opinion on Drug Delivery|volume=9|issue=12|year=2012|page=1525}}</ref>
<ref>[http://www.acoustics.org/press/135th/crum.htm Therapeutic Ultrasound: A Promising Future in Clinical Medicine] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071012222403/http://www.acoustics.org/press/135th/crum.htm |date=2007-10-12 }}</ref>

治療性超聲波在某些領域的有效性還存在爭議。<ref>[http://ptjournal.apta.org/content/81/7/1339.short ''A Review of Therapeutic Ultrasound: Effectiveness Studies''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120224045430/http://ptjournal.apta.org/content/81/7/1339.short |date=2012-02-24 }}</ref>

== 用法==
{{see|理療}}

超聲波可以通過傳感器或者塗藥器來直接接觸人類[[皮膚|皮膚]]。各處皮膚都可以通過塗油來減少摩擦并提高超聲波傳輸效率。理療中的治療性超聲波通過交替壓縮和[[稀疏_(人體)|稀疏]]聲波市值大於20,000周秒赫來發生作用，其頻率與為0.7至3.3 [[MHz|MHz]]。影響程度向隨著深度遞減，該聲波主要由[[結締組織|結締組織]]，例如[[韌帶|韌帶]]、[[腱|腱]]和[[筋膜|筋膜]]等接受，[[肉芽組織|肉芽組織]]也可接受治療性超聲波。.<ref>[http://www.electrotherapy.org/electro/ultrasound/therapeutic_ultrasound.htm Watson, T. (2006). "Therapeutic Ultrasound".] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070821214858/http://www.electrotherapy.org/electro/ultrasound/therapeutic_ultrasound.htm |date=2007-08-21 }} (see [http://www.electrotherapy.org/electro/downloads/Therapeutic%20Ultrasound.pdf here] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070412093629/http://www.electrotherapy.org/electro/downloads/Therapeutic%20Ultrasound.pdf |date=2007-04-12 }} for a pdf version with the author and date information)</ref>

== 益處 ==

治療性超聲波可以提高治療部位的血液流速、減小疼痛感。<ref name="#1"/>

超聲波產生的[[空穴效應|空穴效應]]導致形成微小氣泡，從而激發[[細胞膜|細胞膜]]的自愈能力。<ref>Wilkin, H. D., et al. (2004). Influence of Therapeutic Ultrasound on Skeletal Muscle Regeneration Following Blunt Contusion. ''International Journal of Sports Medicine, 25, ''73-77.</ref>

